        <p class="TableTextEmphasis">mc-feader-type</p>
        <p class="TableText">This property is used with the MadCap|pageFooter and MadCap|pageHeader styles when building <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.Word" /> output. This property specifies which types of pages a page footer or header is displayed on (all, even pages, first page, odd pages). You can always override the page type used at the spot where a particular page footer or header proxy is inserted. This setting simply lets you control the default setting.</p>
        <p class="TableText" MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">
            <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Printed-Output/Other-Activities/Editing-Page-Type1.htm">Specifying the Page Type for Page Footers and Headers</MadCap:xref>
        </p>
    </body>
</html>